to the editor thomas lynch how mourners were betrayed op ed feb 22 grants that some favor cremation as a way to return their dead to nature but argues that many others see cremation as avoiding all that fuss part of that fuss is the ludicrous cost of burial and all its attendant equipment pushed by the funeral industry coffins burial clothes embalming hearses plots markers other parts of that fuss include the enormous amount of land and water needed for cemeteries the thought of burying and saving a corpse to have it decay in a sealed coffin is repellent i do not need to visit a grave to remember my parents i carry my memories of them with me every day the fact that i did not witness their cremations matters not at all judith r birnberg sherman oaks calif feb 23 2002

